# first ignore everything
**

# explictly add exceptions for required files/paths
!src/**/*.cs
!**/*.csproj
!**/appsettings.*
!global.json
!**/*.props
!**/*.targets

# custom
!**/*.lua
!**/*.instructions.md
!wait-for-it.sh
!ffmpeg-record.sh

# Debug builds (Dockerfile.Debug) sync the local sibling repos into deps/.
# Include their full source tree so project references resolve.
!deps/**

# never leak build output, VCS metadata, or local-only secrets into the image.
# Excluding bin/obj repo-wide also keeps generated files (e.g. *.AssemblyInfo.cs,
# *.GlobalUsings.g.cs, *.nuget.g.props) — which the allow-list above would otherwise
# re-include — out of the context so they don't bust the restore/COPY layer cache.
**/bin
**/obj
**/.git
**/.vs
**/appsettings.Local*.json

# test projects are never part of the runtime image; excluding the *.Tests dirs
# keeps them out of the csproj globs / COPY and avoids cache busts on test edits
**/*.Tests
